			<h2>1st Granite, 257</h2>
			<p><span style="font-family: 'Glass Antiqua', cursive; font-size: 48px;">T</span>They classify these days as early spring.  While the trees continue to blow in the wind, and birds sing to... whoever the hell they sing to, a dark mist spreads through the hallways today.  I have been concerned of the rumblings outside of our walls for days.  Bolange, our previous overseer, had previously been acting in his usual queer way, but yesterday came screaming through the hallways.  I heard the commotion and was annoyed.  I just wanted to drink some mead and do regular dwarf things like fart and chew on my toe nails.  I happen to step out precisely at the time he got to my door.  He pleaded with me to take the reins of this failure he calls a fortress and to take care of the army of goblins outside of our very gate.</p>
